ctly how I feel about&nbsp;<code style='box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15px; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, \"Courier New\", Courier, monospace;'>async</code> and&nbsp;<code style='box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15px; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, \"Courier New\", Courier, monospace;'>await</code>.&nbsp;<mark style=\"box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; background-color: rgb(232, 243, 232); color: currentcolor;\">If you wait for&nbsp;</mark><mark style=\"box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; background-color: rgb(232, 243, 232); color: currentcolor;\"><code style='box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15px; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, \"Courier New\", Courier, monospace;'>async</code></mark><mark style=\"box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; background-color: rgb(232, 243, 232); color: currentcolor;\">&nbsp;code your function now has to be&nbsp;</mark><mark style=\"box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; background-color: rgb(232, 243, 232); color: currentcolor;\"><code style='box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15px; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, \"Courier New\", Courier, monospace;'>async</code></mark><mark style=\"box-sizing: inherit; cursor: pointer; background-color: rgb(232, 243, 232); color: currentcolor;\">&nbsp;as well.</mark> And if there&rsquo;s any function relying on that function that code also has to be&nbsp;<code style='box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15px; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, \"Courier New\", Courier, monospace;'>async</code> and on and on and on. Until you reach the top level.</p><p data-selectable-paragraph=\"\" style='box-sizing: inherit; margin: 2.14em 0px -0.46em; font-weight: 400; color: rgb(36, 36, 36); word-break: break-word; font-style: normal; line-height: 32px; letter-spacing: -0.003em; font-family: source-serif-pro, Georgia, Cambria, \"Times New Roman\", Times, serif; font-size: 20px; font-variant-ligatures: normal; font-variant-caps: normal; orphans: 2; text-align: start; text-indent: 0px; text-transform: none; widows: 2; word-spacing: 0px; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px; white-space: normal; background-color: rgb(255, 255, 255); text-decoration-thickness: initial; text-decoration-style: initial; text-decoration-color: initial;'>I&rsquo;ve always hated this. But there&rsquo;s no better way to do this. It&rsquo;s a necessary evil. Right..? Well, I&rsquo;ve recently been coding a lot in Go. And Go does not have&nbsp;<code style='box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15px; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, \"Courier New\", Courier, monospace;'>async</code> and&nbsp;<code style='box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 400; background-color: rgb(242, 242, 242); padding: 2px 4px; font-size: 15px; font-family: source-code-pro, Menlo, Monaco, \"Courier New\", Courier, monospace;'>await</code>. And this is despite it being famous for its concurrency. And you know what? I really like it.</p>",
